<div id="review_2860651431" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2860651431" />
    <a title="Stephanie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16551543-stephanie"><img alt="Stephanie" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2860651431?book_show_action=true">Jun 16, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Stephanie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Stephanie" href="/user/show/16551543-stephanie">Stephanie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780470553732" href="/book/show/6869746-no-one-would-listen">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2860651431" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1000697348392272829">Yes, this book is not well written or well edited, &quot;principal&quot; is frequently misspelled as &quot;principle&quot; and yes, it gets repetitive at times, but I couldn&apos;t stop reading anyway. The story was gripping enough to keep me going. One striking thing was how Markopolos&apos;s bosses at Rampart kept pressuring him to come up with an investment product that could compete with Madoff&apos;s. Markopolos had the quantitative skills to know this wasn&apos;t possible, unless his bosses wanted to start their own Ponzi scheme</span>
  <span id="freeText1000697348392272829" style="display:none">Yes, this book is not well written or well edited, "principal" is frequently misspelled as "principle" and yes, it gets repetitive at times, but I couldn't stop reading anyway. The story was gripping enough to keep me going. One striking thing was how Markopolos's bosses at Rampart kept pressuring him to come up with an investment product that could compete with Madoff's. Markopolos had the quantitative skills to know this wasn't possible, unless his bosses wanted to start their own Ponzi scheme or front-running scheme. They wouldn't listen to him, though. Managerial incompetence at its finest. The incompetence of the SEC as described is this book is of a different order of magnitude. Interesting to learn how many people must have known something was wrong but didn't ask any questions as long as the checks kept coming, or said "No thank you" to Madoff and left it at that. Sobering that since Markopolos and his team were focusing on feeder funds, they had no idea (until Madoff crashed) that many individual investors were being scammed as well.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1000697348392272829" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


